Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: client
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Inner client responsible for uploading events, automatically initialized. Additional parameters like request retrying could be configured here.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: defaultDatabase
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: The destination database for events that doesn’t specify one, default is “td”.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: defaultTable
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: The destination table for events that doesn’t specify one. Currently this also applied for automatically tracked events (if enabled): app lifecycle, IAP and audits, default is “td_ios”.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: cdpEndpoint
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: The host to use for the Profile API

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +initializeWithApiKey:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Initialize TreasureData.sharedInstance with the default API endpoint “https://us01.records.in.treasuredata.com”.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +initializeWithApiKey:apiEndpoint:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Initialize TreasureData.sharedInstance

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +initializeEncryptionKey:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Encrypted the event data in the local persisted buffer.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +sharedInstance
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: The default singleton SDK instance.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -initWithApiKey:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Construct a new TreasureData instance with the default API endpoint “https://us01.records.in.treasuredata.com”.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -initWithApiKey:apiEndpoint:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Construct a new TreasureData instance.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -addEvent:database:table:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Track a new event

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -addEvent:table:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Track a new event targets TreasureData.defaultDatabase

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -addEventWithCallback:database:table:onSuccess:onError:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Track a new event with status handlers.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -addEventWithCallback:table:onSuccess:onError:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Same as -[TreasureData addEventWithCallback:database:table:onSuccess:onError], targets the TreasureData.defaultDatabase.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -uploadEventsWithCallback:onError:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Same as -[TreasureData addEventWithCallback:database:table:onSuccess:onError], targets the TreasureData.defaultDatabase / TreasureData.defaultTable.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -uploadEvents
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Same as -[TreasureData uploadEventWithCallback:onError:] but ignores the result status.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -getUUID
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Get UUID generated from TreasureData. The value will be set to td_uuid column for every events if enableAutoAppendUniqId is called.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAutoAppendUniqId
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Automaticaly append td_uuid column for every events. The value is randomly generated and persisted, it is shared across app launches and events. Basically, it is used to prepresent for a unique app installation instance.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableAutoAppendUniqId
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable the auto appended td_uuid column.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -resetUniqId
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Permanently reset the appended td_uuid column to a different value.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAutoAppendLocalTimestamp:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Automatically append the local time value when the event is added. Enabled by default.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAutoAppendLocalTimestamp
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Automatically append the local time when the event is added. By default, the column’s name is “time”

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableAutoAppendLocalTimestamp
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable automatically append the local time when the event is added.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAutoAppendModelInformation
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable these auto appended columns:

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableAutoAppendModelInformation
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable the auto appended td_device, td_model, td_os_version, td_os_type columns.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAutoAppendAppInformation
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Automatically append these columns:

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableAutoAppendAppInformation
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable these auto appended td_app_ver and td_app_ver_num column

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAutoAppendLocaleInformation
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Automatically append these columns:

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableAutoAppendLocaleInformation
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable the auto appended td_locale_country and td_locale_language columns.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAutoAppendRecordUUID:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Automatically append a random and unique ID for each event. Disabled by default.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAutoAppendRecordUUID
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Same as `-[TreasureData enableAutoAppendRecordUUID:], using “record_uuid” as the column name.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableAutoAppendRecordUUID
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable appending ID for each event.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAutoAppendAdvertisingIdentifier
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Automatically append device’s advertising identifer, a.k.a IDFA, using “td_maid” as the default column name.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAutoAppendAdvertisingIdentifier:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Automatically append device’s advertising identifer, a.k.a IDFA.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableAutoAppendAdvertisingIdentifier
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable automatically append device’s advertising identifer, a.k.a IDFA.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -startSession:database:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Start to a new session for this TreasureData‘s instance

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -startSession:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Same as -[TreasureData startSession:database:], using TreasureData.defaultDatabase as the destination database for td_session_event.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -endSession:database:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: End this TresureData instance’s session. Track an additional event of {"td_session_event": "end"} to the specified database and table.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -endSession:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Same as -[TreasureData endSession], using TreasureData.defaultDatbase as the destination database for td_session_event.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -getSessionId
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Get this instance’s current session ID.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +startSession
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Start a static session that is shared across TreasureData instances. Unlike instance’s session, there will be no td_session_event tracked.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +endSession
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: End the current static session. Unlike instance’s session, there will be no td_session_event tracked.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +getSessionId
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Get the current static session ID.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +resetSessionId
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Reset static session. This will force create a new session when static method startSession is called.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +setSessionTimeoutMilli:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Set the minimal time window that the static session stays alive.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableCustomEvent
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Re-enable custom events collection if previously disabled

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableCustomEvent
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable custom events collection (ones that called manually with addEvent...).

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -isCustomEventEnabled
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Whether the custom events collection is allowed or not.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableAppLifecycleEvent
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Enable tracking app lifecycle events. This setting is persited, default is disabled.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableAppLifecycleEvent
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Same as disableCustomEvent, this is supposed to be called for your users to opt-out of the automatic tracking.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -isAppLifecycleEventEnabled
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Whether the app lifecycle events collection is allowed or not

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableInAppPurchaseEvent
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Enable tracking SKPaymentTransactionStatePurchased event automatically. This is disabled by default. Unlike custom and app lifecycle events, this settings is not persisted.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableInAppPurchaseEvent
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable tracking IAP events

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -isInAppPurchaseEventEnabled
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Whether this TreasureData‘s instance tracking IAP events

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -fetchUserSegments:keys:options:completionHandler:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Fetch user segments from cdp endpoint. Callback with either a JSON serialized object or an error.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -setDefaultValue:forKey:database:table:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Set default value for key in all new events targeting database and table.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -defaultValueForKey:database:table:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Get default value of key in all new events targeting database and table.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -removeDefaultValueForKey:database:table:
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Remove default value of key in all new events targeting database and table.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -enableRetryUploading
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Enable retrying on failed uploads. Already enabled by default.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: -disableRetryUploading
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Do not attempt to retry on failed uploads.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +enableEventCompression
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Event data will be compressed with zlib before uploading to server.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +disableEventCompression
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Event data will be uploaded in it’s full format.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +enableLogging
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Enable client logging. Disabled by default.

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +disableLogging
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable client’s logging/

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +enableTraceLogging
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Enable trace logging

Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.name: +disableTraceLogging
Classes/TreasureData.html#/c:objc(cs)Tre.abstract: Disable trace logging

Classes/TDClient.html.name: TDClient
Classes/TDClient.html.abstract: The internal client using for sending requests. Most of the exposed properties could be configured via the container TreasureData instance. You probably need this only to tuning the retry parameters.

Classes/TreasureData.html.name: TreasureData
Classes/TreasureData.html.abstract: The main interface for the SDK. All initialization and configuration (except retry parameters) could be done through here.
